text:
e="preserve">Susan Eileen McDonald (born 7 February 1970) is an Australian politician and businesswoman. She has served as a Senator for Queensland since the 2019 federal election. She is a member of the Liberal National Party of Queensland and sits with the National Party in federal parliament. She was born in Brisbane, Queensland.
On 16 March 2020, during the 2019–20 coronavirus pandemic, it was made clear that McDonald had tested positive to COVID-19.
